  "_about": "AirDriver chipset database. Maps USB/PCI VID:PID -> chipset -> driver install strategy. 'usb_ids' are lowercase 'vid:pid' (works for PCI ids too). 'kernel_native' tells AirDriver when an in-kernel driver already exists so it can SKIP a pointless DKMS build. 'drivers' are tried in 'priority' order (1 = first). 'monitor_mode'/'injection' are honest capability flags for pentest use; some chips connect fine but can't inject. Extend freely: add entries or usb_ids and AirDriver picks them up on next scan. PRs welcome at https://github.com/at0m-b0mb/AirDriver.",
